The paper proposes a regularizer for reinforcement learning that focuses on reproducing past good trajectories, which can potentially make long-term credit assignment easier when rewards are sparse and delayed. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
